    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put​(K key,
                V value)
        Description copied from interface: HashTable
        Inserts the pair <key, value> into this. The container should not allow for null keys and values, and we will test if you are throwing a IllegalArgumentException from your code if this method is given null arguments! It is important that we establish that no null entries can exist in our database because the semantics of HashTable.get(Object) and HashTable.remove(Object) are that they return null if, and only if, their key parameter is null. This method is expected to run in amortized constant time.
        Specified by:
        put in interface HashTable<K,V>
        Parameters:
        key - The record's key.
        value - The record's value.

      • capacity

        public int capacity()
        Description copied from interface: HashTable
        Returns the capacity of this HashTable. In Separate Chaining, this is the total number of cells from which the lists begin. In Open Addressing methods, this method returns the size of the underlying array. As a consequence, in SeparateChainingHashTable, it's possible for HashTable.size() to return a value larger than this method. On the other hand, for Open Addressing methods like LinearProbingHashTable and QuadraticProbingHashTable, the value returned by this method is an upper bound on the value returned by HashTable.size().
        Specified by:
        capacity in interface HashTable<K,V>
        Returns:
        the number of cells in the table.
